Class Lvalue

  • java.lang.Object
    • absyn.Absyn
      • absyn.Expression
        • absyn.Lvalue
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayAccess, FieldAccess, Variable

    public abstract class Lvalue
extends Expression
    A node of abstract syntax representing a leftvalue, that is, an expression which refers to the container of a value, and which can hence be used on the left of an assignment.
    Author:
    Fausto Spoto

    • Method Detail

      • translateBeforeAssignment

        public abstract Block translateBeforeAssignment(CodeSignature where,
                                                Block continuation)
        Generates the intermediate Kitten code which must be executed before the evaluation of the rightvalue which is going to be assigned to this leftvalue.
        Parameters:
        where - the method or constructor where this expression occurs
        continuation - the code which must be executed after this expression. Usually, this is the code that evaluates a rightvalue in an assignment
        Returns:
        a code that is executed before the evaluation of a rightvalue that is going to be assigned to this leftvalue, followed by continuation
